p: The major compounds of P. cubeba EO were terpinen-4-ol (42.41%), followed by α-copaene (20.04%), γ-elemene (17.68%), α-cubebene (6.54%), and D-germacrene (2.50%). Whereas P. nigrum EO contained the dominant components of β-caryophyllene (51.12%), β-thujene (20.58%), β-selinene (5.59%), δ-eIemene (5.03%), and α-copaene (4.79%).
